cturn.</li>\n</ol>\n<div class="yarpp-related-rss">\n<p>Related posts:<ol>\n<li><a href="http://www.wptavern.com/sitepoint-gives-primer-on-parent-child-themes" rel="bookmark" title="SitePoint Gives Primer On Parent Child Themes">SitePoint Gives Primer On Parent Child Themes</a></li>\n<li><a href="http://www.wptavern.com/wordpress-themes-in-2009" rel="bookmark" title="WordPress Themes In 2009">WordPress Themes In 2009</a></li>\n<li><a href="http://www.wptavern.com/what-exactly-is-the-carrington-framework" rel="bookmark" title="What Exactly Is The Carrington Framework?">What Exactly Is The Carrington Framework?</a></li>\n</ol></p>\n</div>\n<img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/WordpressTavern/~4/UDgPQ9fcSiY" height="1" width="1" />";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Wed, 12 Dec 2012 19:41:42 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:6:"Jeffro";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:42;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:13:"\n	\n	\n	\n	\n	\n	\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:2:{s:0:"";a:5:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:42:"WPTavern: CodePoet Interviews Mika Epstein";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"http://www.wptavern.com/?p=6728";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:94:"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/WordpressTavern/~3/JMiQ8kFjzO0/codepoet-interviews-mika-epstein";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1249:"<p>CodePoet has <a href="http://build.codepoet.com/2012/12/11/mika-epstein-interview/">published a great interview</a> with WordPress support extraordinaire , Mika Epstein also known as <a href="http://profiles.wordpress.org/ipstenu">Ipstenu</a>. The interview covers the basics of how she got involved with the web and WordPress. While the interview is great, I&#8217;ll take her last words as a great piece of advice.</p>\n<blockquote><p>Remember to have a life, remember you can say no, and remember to ask for help.</p></blockquote>\n<p>Thanks Mika for all you do to help make WordPress better. Be sure to check out her <a href="http://halfelf.org/ebooks/">eBooks</a> if you&#8217;re looking for help on using WordPress Multisite. </p>\n<div class="yarpp-related-rss">\n<p>Related posts:<ol>\n<li><a href="http://www.wptavern.com/bornrich-interviews-matt-mullenweg" rel="bookmark" title="BornRich Interviews Matt Mullenweg">BornRich Interviews Matt Mullenweg</a></li>\n<li><a href="http://www.wptavern.com/lexnet-interviews-matt-mullenweg" rel="bookmark" title="Lexnet Interviews Matt Mullenweg">Lexnet Interviews Matt Mullenweg</a></li>\n</ol></p>\n</div>\n<img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/WordpressTavern/~4/JMiQ8kFjzO0" height="1" width="1" />";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Wed, 12 Dec 2012 19:32:14 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:6:"Jeffro";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:43;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:13:"\n	\n	\n	\n	\n	\n	\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:2:{s:0:"";a:5:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:32:"WPTavern: bbPress 2.2.3 Released";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"http://www.wptavern.com/?p=6725";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:84:"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/WordpressTavern/~3/Rl4Hl3tkyn8/bbpress-2-2-3-released";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1552:"<p><a href="http://www.wptavern.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/05/bbpress.png" rel="thumbnail"><img src="http://www.wptavern.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/05/bbpress.png" alt="bbpress.org logo" width="207" height="73" class="alignright size-full wp-image-1269" /></a>The latest version of<a href="http://bbpress.org/blog/2012/12/bbpress-2-2-3-released/"> bbPress was released</a> on the same day as WordPress 3.5. The new version sports a few bug fixes with themes and BuddyPress compatibility. On the topic if bbPress, there is also news that Jennifer M. Dodd has been <a href="http://bbpress.org/blog/2012/12/introducing-jmdodd/">officially given committ access</a> to the bbPress project. One her tasks for bbPress 2.3 is full forum search. Something of which you can keep tabs on by following <a href="http://bbpress.trac.wordpress.org/ticket/1575">ticket 1515</a>.</p>\n<div class="yarpp-related-rss">\n<p>Related posts:<ol>\n<li><a href="http://www.wptavern.com/bbpress-now-has-an-official-plugin" rel="bookmark" title="bbPress Now Has An Official Plugin">bbPress Now Has An Official Plugin</a></li>\n<li><a href="http://www.wptavern.com/buddypress-and-bbpress-are-getting-a-divorce" rel="bookmark" title="BuddyPress And bbPress Are Getting A Divorce">BuddyPress And bbPress Are Getting A Divorce</a></li>\n<li><a href="http://www.wptavern.com/bbpress-rc-5-released" rel="bookmark" title="bbPress RC 5 Released">bbPress RC 5 Released</a></li>\n</ol></p>\n</div>\n<img src